    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="349"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.001B14.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Chargé <persName type="to">White</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 92.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I enclose, with office copy, a letter addressed
                    by the President to His Excellency Dr. Ramón Báez,<note n="7" xml:id="d349fn7"
                        >Not printed.</note> acknowledging the receipt of his letter of August 27
                    last in which he announced his assumption of the Presidency of the Dominican
                    Republic and his entrance upon the duties of that office.</p>
                <p>You will forward the copy to the Foreign Office and deliver the original in the
                    manner most agreeable to His Excellency.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
